On April 7, 2013, aged 81, Pulitzer-Rousseau died at her home in Palm Beach, Florida.[19]When Her son Peter spoke at her funeral service saying, "Our mother was a woman of extremes…She gave and gave and gave, and asked for nothing in return…. Joyous feelings just oozed out of her…. She showed us how to enjoy life."[20]
